Azure App Service supports different types of applications:

* Web Apps: Host websites and web applications
* API Apps: Build and host RESTful APIs
* WebJobs: Run background tasks or scripts
* Mobile Apps: Backend services for mobile applications

For example, a company can use Web Apps for its website, API Apps for backend services, and WebJobs for background processing.

A real-life use case is an e-commerce platform where:

* Web App handles frontend
* API App manages backend logic
* WebJobs process orders
* Mobile App supports mobile users

This flexibility allows building complete application ecosystems within Azure App Service.
